==Old English==
===Etymology===
Probably a weak variant of [[faran]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'fe:ɹan/

===Verb===
'''fēran''' (class 1 weak)
# to [[go]], to [[travel]] or [[journey]]
#:''Ic fere geond foldan'': I travel across the earth.
# to set out, to [[leave]] or [[depart]]
#:''He on morne feran wolde'': he wished to leave in the morning.

